statistics.name: assists
statistics.description: The number of times a player who passes the ball to a teammate in a way that leads to a score by field goal, meaning that he or she was "assisting" in the basket. There is some judgment involved in deciding whether a passer should be credited with an assist.

statistics.description: The number of times a player loses possession to the other team.

statistics.name: assistTurnoverRatio

article.headline: Cornell 73, Penn St. Behrend 49
article.story: ITHACA, N.Y. -- Jeff Foote scored 22 points to lead Cornell to a 73-49 victory over Penn State Behrend on Thursday. Foote was 10-for-12 from the floor and added seven rebounds, two assists and two blocked shots in 16 minutes as 10 players scored and 16 saw action for the Big Red (11-2), who extended their winning streak to nine games. Max Groebe added 15 points and Ryan Wittman scored 10 for Cornell, which matched its best start through 13 games. The Big Red shot 56.3 percent from the floor, was 11-for-24 from 3-point range (46 percent) and outrebounded the Division III Lions 36-27. Cornell led 40-26 at halftime and extended the margin to 51-31 on Foote's dunk with 15:46 to play in the game. The Big Red built the lead to 68-38 on Andre Wilkins' jumper with 5:12 remaining. Chris Wroblewski had eight assists for Cornell. Adam Kaiser led the Lions (5-3) with nine points.
